<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1436,1710,2026]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
1. Male............................................................................................... 
<specimenCount pageId="86" pageNumber="87" type="female">2 Female</specimenCount>
............................................................................................ 14
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1436,1710,2026]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
2. Light organs absent; very dark brown to black species with pronounced posterolateral eye emargination; known only from 
<collectingCountry name="New Caledonia" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" box="[336,612,1798,1820]" firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref114597" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2013) Systematics and phylogenetics of Indo-Pacific Luciolinae fireflies (Coleoptera: Lampyridae) and the description of new genera. Zootaxa, 3653 (1), 1 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3653.1.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin 2013</bibRefCitation>
figs 120 121, 124, 125)............................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Ballantyne Light" authorityName="Ballantyne Light" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculofissa">
<emphasis box="[1229,1326,1798,1819]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">oculofissa</emphasis>
Ballantyne Light
</taxonomicName>
organs present in at least one abdominal ventrite; eye emargination present or not............................. 3
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1436,1710,2026]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
3. Eyes with strong posterolateral emargination clearly visible in resting head (
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" box="[957,1234,1857,1879]" firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref114597" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2013) Systematics and phylogenetics of Indo-Pacific Luciolinae fireflies (Coleoptera: Lampyridae) and the description of new genera. Zootaxa, 3653 (1), 1 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3653.1.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin 2013</bibRefCitation>
fig. 110)....... 4 Eyes without a visible posterolateral emargination, or with a weak emargination usually covered by the pronotum........ 5
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1436,1710,2026]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
4. No light organs in 
<date box="[405,437,1916,1937]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">V7</date>
; light organs in 
<date box="[591,620,1916,1938]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">V6</date>
reduced to anterolateral plaques; known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[1117,1150,1916,1938]" name="Fiji" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fiji</collectingCountry>
......... 
<taxonomicName authority="Olivier Light" authorityName="Olivier Light" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypocrita">
<emphasis box="[1270,1362,1916,1937]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">hypocrita</emphasis>
Olivier Light
</taxonomicName>
organs in both 
<date box="[426,514,1945,1967]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">V6 and 7</date>
entire, may be retracted from lateral margins (
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" box="[961,1238,1945,1967]" firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref114597" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2013) Systematics and phylogenetics of Indo-Pacific Luciolinae fireflies (Coleoptera: Lampyridae) and the description of new genera. Zootaxa, 3653 (1), 1 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3653.1.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin 2013</bibRefCitation>
figs 114, 119)....................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Bourgeois" authorityName="Bourgeois" authorityYear="1884" box="[1229,1436,1974,1996]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antipodum">
<emphasis box="[1229,1332,1974,1995]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">antipodum</emphasis>
Bourgeois
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1436,1710,2026]" lastBlockId="87.[151,1437,153,1026]" lastPageId="87" lastPageNumber="88" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">5. Dorsal surface completely black or very dark brown.......................................................... 6 Dorsal surface never completely dark brown; pronotum usually pale coloured sometimes with a median dark marking..... 7</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1437,153,1026]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
6. Known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[407,560,183,205]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
; aedeagal LL widely separated along their inner dorsal margins with a rounded projection along inner dorsal margins approximately half their length from their apices (
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" box="[967,1244,212,234]" firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref114597" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2013) Systematics and phylogenetics of Indo-Pacific Luciolinae fireflies (Coleoptera: Lampyridae) and the description of new genera. Zootaxa, 3653 (1), 1 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3653.1.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin 2013</bibRefCitation>
figs 111, 112)...................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Ballantyne A S. E." authorityName="Ballantyne A S. E." class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilaclara">
<emphasis box="[1214,1326,241,262]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">aquilaclara</emphasis>
Ballantyne A S. E.
</taxonomicName>
Asian species sometimes from high altitudes; aedeagal LL not widely separated along their inner dorsal margins and without rounded projection as described above (
<figureCitation box="[688,769,300,322]" captionStart="FIGURES 305−308" captionStartId="98.[151,264,950,975]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,166,924]" captionTargetId="figure@98.[151,1435,166,930]" captionTargetPageId="98" captionText="FIGURES 305−308. Luciola pallidipes male. 305−308 aedeagal sheath: 305 dorsal (arrow indicates prolonged margin of sheath tergite; aedeagus removed); 306−308 aedeagal sheath with aedeagus: 306 right lateral (arrow indicates prolonged margin of sheath tergite); 307 dorsal; 308 ventral (arrows indicate leaf like lobes from LL of aedeagus). Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508218/files/figure.png" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Fig. 307</figureCitation>
)........................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1928" box="[1305,1437,300,322]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidipes">
<emphasis box="[1305,1400,300,321]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">pallidipes</emphasis>
Pic
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1437,153,1026]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">7. Dorsal surface pale yellowish brown with dark elytral apices....................................................8 Dorsal surface not as above; pronotum may be black; elytra usually dark brown to black............................. 9</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1437,153,1026]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
8. Ventral abdomen with median brown markings on 
<date box="[713,766,388,410]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">V4–5</date>
with lateral margins converging anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1323,388,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 270−279" captionStartId="93.[151,264,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,194,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@93.[203,1385,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="93" captionText="FIGURES 270−279. Luciola jengai sp. nov. type males. 270, 273 habitus dorsal; 271, 272 habitus ventral; 274, 275 abdomen: 274 dorsal; 275 ventral; 276 tergite 8 and aedeagal sheath ventral; 277−279 aedeagus: 277 dorsal; 279 ventral; 279 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508206/files/figure.png" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Figs 271, 275</figureCitation>
)........................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Nada" authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" box="[1237,1354,417,439]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jengai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1237,1297,418,439]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">jengai</emphasis>
Nada
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1360,1436,418,439]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1436,418,439]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Ventral abdomen not coloured as above; ventrites anterior to the LO yellowish except for dark posterior margin of 
<date box="[1353,1383,447,469]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">V5</date>
(Fig. 285)................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Jusoh" authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" box="[1250,1354,476,498]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niah" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1250,1293,476,497]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">niah</emphasis>
Jusoh
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1360,1436,476,497]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1436,476,497]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1437,153,1026]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
