<figureCitation box="[551,733,828,850]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Figs 258, 266, 267</figureCitation>
