<figureCitation box="[366,502,887,909]" captionStart="FIGURES 246−257" captionStartId="88.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,166,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@88.[214,1374,166,1872]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="FIGURES 246−257. Luciola chapaensis males. 246, 253 Luciola atripes type MNHN; 247 Luciola chapaensis type male MNHN; 248−251, 254−257 Malaysia Kelantan males; 246 elytra; 247, 248 habitus dorsal; 249 habitus ventral; 250, 251 abdo- men: 250 ventral; 251 dorsal; 254−256 aedeagus: 254 ventral; 255 dorsal; 256 left lateral; 257 aedeagal sheath dorsal (arrow indicates area of prolongation of sheath tergite). Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508202/files/figure.png" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Figs 246−247</figureCitation>
)........................................................... 
